title: Easy: Sum of Multiples
description: Write a function `sum_of_multiples` that finds the sum of all unique multiples of 3 or 5 below a given number `n`. Your function should take an integer `n` as input and return the sum of all unique multiples of 3 or 5 less than `n`.#### Function Signature```pythondef sum_of_multiples(n: int) -> int:`#### Input- `n` (int): An integer greater than 0.#### Output- Returns an integer that is the sum of all unique multiples of 3 or 5 less than `n`.
code:
def sum_of_multiples(n: int) -> int:
    return sum({i for i in range(1, n) if i % 3 == 0 or i % 5 == 0})
